tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows markedly elevated creatinine, proteinuria, and abnormal urine findings (cloudy, brown, low specific gravity, ketonuria, bilirubinuria), suggesting significant renal dysfunction, possibly acute or chronic kidney disease. Low HbA1c and normal glucose argue against diabetes. No evidence of urinary tract infection. Recommend urgent nephrology evaluation and further workup for underlying renal pathology.
